annotationA: 28S ribosomal protein S15, mitochondrial; Essential for gut mitochondrial activity. Might be involved in tissue specific growth factor production; Belongs to the universal ribosomal protein uS15 family
annotationB: 40S ribosomal protein S11; Structural constituent of ribosome. It is involved in the biological process described with: mitotic spindle elongation; translation; mitotic spindle organization; neurogenesis; Belongs to the universal ribosomal protein uS17 family
